Example 6 chudu konchem diffga – Control Flow in Procedures
-- Stored procedures can include logic like IF statements
Example: classify diff. rent
DELIMITER //
CREATE PROCEDURE classify_rent(IN rent_value INT)
BEGIN
IF rent_value > 70000 THEN
    SELECT 'Luxury Property';
ELSEIF rent_value > 40000 THEN
    SELECT 'Mid Range Property';
ELSEIF rent_value = 20000 THEN
    SELECT 'Exactly 20k Rent';
ELSE
    SELECT 'Budget Property';
END IF;
END //
DELIMITER ;
CALL classify_rent(60000);

Example 6 – Procedure on agg. Analytics
-- Generate locality rent report
DELIMITER //
CREATE PROCEDURE locality_rent_report()
BEGIN
SELECT locality,
       COUNT(*) AS total_properties,
       AVG(rent) AS avg_rent
FROM properties
GROUP BY locality
ORDER BY avg_rent DESC;
END //

DELIMITER ; -- Used in real estate analytics dashboards gamaninchaara eppudina

Example 7 – Updating Data
-- Increase rent for a locality
DELIMITER //
CREATE PROCEDURE increase_rent_by_locality(
    IN loc VARCHAR(100),
    IN percent_increase INT
)
BEGIN
UPDATE properties
SET rent = rent + (rent * percent_increase / 100)
WHERE locality = loc;
END //
DELIMITER ;

CALL increase_rent_by_locality('Whitefield',10);

Viewing Stored Procedures (SP)
SHOW PROCEDURE STATUS; -- List all procedures
SHOW CREATE PROCEDURE procedure_name; -- See definition

DROP PROCEDURE procedure_name; -- Dropping an SP

When to Use Stored Procedures
- the same query runs frequently
- multiple SQL steps are required
- business rules/result must stay in the database
- automation is needed

--> Finalga Stored procedures help convert SQL queries into reusable programs inside the database
IN - You give a notebook to someone to give input
OUT - They give you a new notebook to write
INOUT - You give your notebook, they write in it and return the same notebook
